The concern is: does the first mount's hashchange listener get cleaned up? The answer is yes — `render-orchestrator.init()` tears down the previous listener:

```typescript
if (unsubscribe !== null) {
    unsubscribe();
    unsubscribe = null;
}
unsubscribe = subscribe(render);
```

So each re-mount properly cleans up the previous mount's listener. This is what the render-orchestration tests verify.

